    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Walls often found in gardens, usually whitewashed, also referred to as an “undulating wall.” The top of the wall has a rhythmical, wave-like appearance, and is covered by small dark tiles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
